#!/bin/bash
# GNAR command reference
cat << 'EOF'
=== GNAR Help ===

Core
  gnar-info                   System information (fastfetch)
  gnar-update                 Update system
  gnar-help                   This reference
  gnar-dashboard              Multi-pane tmux dashboard (btop + sites +
                              docker/pm2 + Claude stats)
  gnar-services-status        Caddy sites + service health (one-shot)
  gnar-claude-stats           Claude Code session + token stats

System info / status
  ff, nf                      fastfetch
  myip                        Public IP
  localip                     Local IPv4 addresses
  ports                       Listening sockets (ss -tulpn)
  system-status               System overview
  db-status                   PostgreSQL + Valkey status
  security-status             UFW + fail2ban + sshd
  port-check <port>           Check if port is in use

Caddy
  add-site <name> [port|dir]  Add site (port = reverse proxy, dir = static files)
  remove-site <name>          Remove site
  list-sites                  List configured sites
  test-caddy                  Validate Caddyfile
  caddy-edit                  Edit Caddyfile
  caddy-reload                Reload Caddy
  caddy-restart               Restart Caddy
  caddy-logs                  Tail Caddy logs
  caddy-status                Caddy systemd + recent logs

PM2
  pm2-start <ecosystem>       Start PM2 app
  pm2-add-site <name> <port> <ecosystem>
  pm2-remove <name>
  pm2-restart <name>
  pm2-logs <name>
  pm2-status                  PM2 + Caddy sites

VS Code Server
  vscode-status (vs)          Status + URL + password
  vscode-restart (vsr)        Restart code-server
  vscode-logs (vsl)           Tail code-server logs
  vscode-password             Print current password
  vscode-change-password <pw>

Kiosk dashboard (attached display)
  Auto-login + Mango (Wayland WM) on tty1; runs `gnar-dashboard` fullscreen.
  Run `gnar-dashboard` from any shell to attach the same session.
  Edit ~/.config/mango/config.conf to change behavior.
  Alt+Return                  Open another foot terminal
  Alt+Q                       Close window
  Super+F                     Toggle fullscreen
  Super+M                     Quit Mango
  Super+Shift+R               Reload mango config

AI / LLM
  claude                      Claude Code CLI (reads ~/CLAUDE.md)
  claude --help               Claude Code usage

Python (uv)
  uv venv                     Create a virtualenv
  uv pip install <pkg>        Install into active venv
  uv tool install <pkg>       Install a Python CLI globally (~/.local/bin)
  uv run <cmd>                Run command in project env

Tmux (prefix: Ctrl-a)
  t                           Start tmux
  tn <name>                   New session
  ta <name>                   Attach
  tl                          List sessions
  tk <name>                   Kill session
  Ctrl-a v / s                Split vertical / horizontal
  Ctrl-a h/j/k/l              Navigate panes

Docker
  dkr / dkc                   docker / docker-compose
  dkps / dkpa                 docker ps / ps -a
  dki                         docker images
  dkex <container>            docker exec -it

Files
  ll / la / lt / lf           eza variants
  tree                        eza --tree
  cat                         bat
  e / edit                    nvim
  mkcd <dir>                  mkdir + cd

Git
  gs ga gc gp gl gd gb gco    git shortcuts
  glog                        git log graph

Navigation
  .. ... .... ..... ......    cd up N levels
  -                           Previous directory
  cdp cdd cdt cdl cde         ~/projects, ~/Downloads, /tmp, /var/log, /etc
  up <n>                      cd up n levels (function)

Help search
  gnar-aliases                fzf over aliases
  gnar-functions              fzf over functions

Backup / scaffolding
  backup-system               Snapshot configs to ~/backups
  create-react-hono <name>    Scaffold React + Hono project

AUR (yay)
  yay-update yay-install yay-remove yay-search yay-info

Snapper (btrfs only)
  snapper -c root list                List snapshots
  snapper -c root create              Manual snapshot
  snapper -c root delete <N>          Delete snapshot N
  snapper -c root undochange A..B     Roll back changes between A and B
  snapper -c root status A..B         Diff snapshots
  Boot stuck after a bad pacman -Syu? Pick a pre-update snapshot from
  GRUB's "Snapshots" submenu.
EOF
